Diagnosis . Males may be distinguished from all other species by the palpal bulb with a short embolus with a small subapical keel (
Figs. 2–5
). Females may be distinguished by the spermathecal receptacula being as wide as long, with apical termini apical (
Fig. 6
).

Description . Male ( MZSP 26076 ). Total length: 21.4 . Carapace: length 8.52 ; width 6.98 . Eye tubercle: length 1.18 ; width 1.52 . Labium: length 0.5 ; width 1.37 . Sternum: length 4.37 ; width 3.65 . Basal segment of chelicera with 8 teeth. Labium with 3 cuspules. Maxilla with 20–23 cuspules. Thoracic fovea slightly recurved. Palp: femur 4.53 / patella 2.9 / tibia 3.43 / cymbium 1.78 / total 12.64 . Legs I : femur 7.8 / patella 4.46 / tibia 5.76 / metatarsus 5.44 / tarsus 3.33 / total 26.79 . II : 6.98 / 3.91 / 5.09 / 4.89 / 3.13 /
